body:
Code like this:
```systemverilog
function automatic integer addr_bit;
    input   [31:0]  a;
    begin
        // addr_bit = 0;
        for (int i = 31; i >= 0; i = i - 1) begin
            if (a[i] == 1'b1) begin
                addr_bit = i;
            end
        end
    end
endfunction

module t;

parameter PP = addr_bit(0);

initial begin
    $write("%d\n", PP);
end

endmodule
```
verilator-4.202 would give Error:
```txt
%Error: Internal Error: t.v:2:28: ../V3Simulate.h:289: No value found for node.
                                : ... In instance t
    2 | function automatic integer addr_bit;
      |                            ^~~~~~~~
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.
```
But VCS can pass this case and PP equals 'X value.
